raw_data.title: Executive
raw_data.description: Senior executive responsible for providing strategic direction, vision, leadership, and program management to the team. Contributes to organizational direction through regular involvement with senior level client leadership and team members. Maintains productive and effective client relationship with the most senior levels of the client organization. Minimum of 20 years senior management experience and Masters Degree required.

raw_data.title: Senior Program Manager
raw_data.description: Manages large complex projects, contracts, funds, and resources (or group of projects, contracts, funds, and resources). Duties may include contract management, large project management, and interface with the customer. The Program Manager serves as the single contract manager, and is the authorized interface with the Government's Contracting Officer's Representative (COR), other Government management personnel, and customer agency representatives. The Senior Program Manager is responsible for formulating and enforcing work standards, assigning contractor schedules, and communicating policies, purposes, and goals to subordinates and subcontractors. Responsible for the overall contract performance and manages services and support operations that may include multiple projects. The Senior Program Manager organizes resources to support multiple concurrent projects and manages the execution of multiple concurrent projects. Minimum of 15 years program management experience and Masters Degree required.

raw_data.title: Program Manager
raw_data.description: Performs overall program planning for projects including: acquisition, technical, business process, information technology, logistics/supply chain management and organizational redesign. The PM serves as the primary interface between the contracting officer and technical representatives. Provides oversight of a multidisciplinary team of technical professionals and is responsible for the project's cost, schedule and technical  performance.  Minimum of 12 years  program management experience and  Bachelors Degree required.

raw_data.title: Senior Consultant
raw_data.description: Performs detailed analysis and planning with knowledge of advanced and complex acquisition/management/logistics concepts, system integration, information technology and business process development. Evaluates engineering/organizational/logistics structure, information technology and business processes for efficiency and effectiveness, and provide documentation of analysis and recommendations for improvement. Primarily the senior level managers in the company and are generally the leaders of Integrated Product Teams (IPTs). Minimum of 8 years experience and Bachelors Degree required.

raw_data.title: Consultant
raw_data.description: Performs detailed analysis and planning with knowledge of advanced acquisition/management/logistics concepts, system integration, information technology and business process development. Evaluates management/organizational/logistics structure, information technology and business processes for efficiency and effectiveness, and provides documentation of analysis and recommendations for improvement. Receives guidance from senior level managers and works independently to accomplish the statement of work contained in the Task Order. Primarily the mid-level managers in the company and are generally the sub leaders of Integrated Product Teams (IPTs). Minimum of 5 years experience and Bachelors Degree required.

raw_data.title: Associate Consultant
raw_data.description: Performs analysis and planning with knowledge of acquisition/management/ logistics concepts, system integration, information technology and business process development. Evaluates management/organizational/logistics structure, information technology and business processes for efficiency and effectiveness, and provides documentation of analysis and recommendations for improvement. Works as part of the consulting team under the direction of either a Senior Consultant or Program Manager in conducting of client work. Primarily the junior level consultants in the company and may be the sub leaders of Integrated Product Teams (IPTs). Minimum of 2 years experience and Bachelor's Degree.

raw_data.title: Analyst
raw_data.description: Applies analytic methodologies and principles to address client’s needs. Interprets results using a variety of techniques, ranging from simple data aggregation via statistical analysis to complex data mining. Designs, develops, implements and maintains business solutions. Analyst functions including data collection, interviewing, data modeling, project testing, and creation of performance measurements to support project objectives. Conducts activities in support of Integrated Product Team's (IPTs) objectives. Works closely with Consultants, Senior Consultants, or Program Managers. Minimum of 1 year experience and Bachelors Degree.

raw_data.title: Administrative Assistant
raw_data.description: Performs administrative duties and responsibilities in support of a program, project, department, or facility. May perform word processing and general secretarial functions. Responsible for administration and adherence to standard policies and procedures such as time charging, expense reporting, and business travel. Under general supervision may collect and analyze data for assigned projects. Requires high school degree.
